<TITLE> Ex-BRTC chief gets 2 years in jail </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 13 (bdnews24.com)  A Dhaka court has sentenced former Bangladesh Road Transport Corporation chairman Taimur Alam Khandaker to two years in jail for not submitting wealth statement to the Anticorruption Commission. As judge Md Ashraf Hossain of the Special Court-5 made the order on Tuesday, Taimur, also a BNP leader, urged the court to allow him rigorous imprisonment. But the judge said a two-year sentence could not be made rigorous. The time Taimur spent in detention would be deducted from his sentence. He notified the court he was arrested on April 18 last year, though the case document showed he was arrested on Aug. 25 that year. The ACC asked the former BRTC chief on Nov. 15, 2007 to give an account of his wealth. As he did not submit wealth statement within the deadline the commission filed a case against him with Lalbagh Police Station on April 4, 2008. b
